Rallies Held to Vow to Implement Tasks Set Forth in Joint New Year Editorial 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- Rallies were held by working people's organizations on Jan. 8 and 9 to vow to implement the militant tasks set forth in the joint New Year editorial. 
 The reporter and speakers at the rally of workers and members of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea held at the plaza in front of the Monument to Party Founding called upon the workers in all fields and at all units including the four pilots of the national economy to carry forward the tradition of the Korean working class who has remained true to the leadership of the Party and perform miracles and innovations in production and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers at the rally of agricultural workers held at the plaza in front of the Tower of the Juche Idea called upon the agricultural workers to devotedly implement the Party's policy on making a revolution in agriculture, keeping up farming as the great foundation of the country true to the militant call of the Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers at the rally of members of the Korean Democratic Women's Union held at the plaza in front of the Monument to Party Founding called upon all the officials and members of the union to demonstrate the invincibility and might of the Songun revolution to the full and positively contribute to turning Juche Korea into a paradise for the people in response to the joint New Year editorial in this significant year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They underscored the need for the members of the women's union to thoroughly establish the trait of attaching importance to the military affairs and conduct dynamic activities to support the army in a bid to consolidate the great army-people unity as firm as a rock. They also called for bringing up sons and daughters as reliable pillars for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the rallies was Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.

Vigorous Reunification Movement Called for in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- Organizations affiliated to the Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration in south Korea reportedly issued resolutions on the occasion of the New Year.
 The Preparatory Committee for the Jeju Regional Solidarity and the Taejon and South Chungchong Provincial Solidarity in their resolutions on Jan. 1 described this year as a historic year in which the Korean nation will win a decisive victory in the fierce confrontation with the U.S. and usher in a new era of independence, democracy and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resolutions called for conducting a more vigorous movement for national reunification under the uplifted banner of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Pusan Regional Solidarity in its resolution on Jan. 2 declared that it would intensify the struggle for peace against the U.S. and war and the struggle for the withdrawal of the U.S. troops from south Korea and against the Grand National Party of south Korea this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Kwangju and South Jolla Provincial Solidarity in its resolution on Jan. 3 said that it would decisively smash any moves of the U.S. and anti-reunification forces threatening the Korean nation, placing the will and interests of the nation above anything else. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Seoul Regional Solidarity in its resolution on Jan. 3 called upon the people of different social strata to glorify the year 2007 as a year of victory through the struggle for peace against the U.S. and war and the struggle for pullback of the U.S. troops and against the GNP.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- A seminar was held at Kim Chaek University of Technology Tuesday to mark the first anniversary of the publication of the famous work of Kim Jong Il "Kim Chaek University of Technology Is Nation's Highest Seat for Training Scientific and Technological Personnel and Pioneer of Revolution in Information Industry."
 Present there were Minister of Education Kim Yong Jin, officials of the ministry, teachers and students of the university. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers said that the work serves as a highly important work as it clarifies the position and role of the university in the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation at present and indicates the way of bringing about a fresh turn in the educational and scientific work at the university to train more able scientific and technological personnel. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the greatness, profundity, justice and vitality of the ideas and theories expounded in the work it provides the university with important guidelines indicating overall ways for successfully performing its mission and tasks as required by the IT age in the new century, the speakers noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Explaining the reason why the work indicates such guidelines, the speakers said the work clarifies fundamental guidelines for preserving and glorifying the immortal leadership exploits of President Kim Il Sung down through generations, clearly shows the main orientation and ways for putting instruction and education at the university on a higher level as required by the IT age and clarifies the issues of adding new facilities to its E-library and gymnasium to improve its appearance.

Implementation of June 15 Joint Declaration Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- Co-chairmen of the All-Korean Committee for Implementation of June 15 Joint Declaration Paek Rak Chong, Kwak Tong Ui and Mun Tong Hwan separately made public articles on Jan. 1 on the occasion of the New Year in which they called for the full implementation of the declaration by pooling wisdom, according to a press report. 
 Paek in his article titled "More Dynamic Movement for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration" wrote that the June 15 Grand Festival for National Reunification and a south-north seminar of mediapersons and other events were successfully held and the June 15 Association of Men of National Literature was inaugurated and sustained efforts were made to push forward the joint work for compiling the "Large Korean Dictionary" last year, adding all this made the Koreans optimistic about the implementation of the joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kwak in his article described this year as a significant year for the movement for national reunification, stressing that the joint declaration should be preserved and implemented in whatever storm and stress as it is a landmark for reunification and to this end it is necessary to achieve the great national unity, guided by the idea of "By our nation itself." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mun in his article wrote that Koreans would preserve the declaration to the last and achieve independent and peaceful reunification.

S. Korean Ministry of Unification Denounced for Separatist Deed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions (KCTU) reportedly released a statement on Jan. 3, denouncing the Ministry of Unification for its reckless acts against national reunification.
 The statement recalled that the ministry disallowed Chairman of the Reunification Committee of the KCTU Jin Kyong Ho's visit to the north for participating in the function of "workers' trip to Mt. Kumgang for peace and reunification against war on the New Year" slated to be held from Jan. 4 to 6. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ministry clarified its stand that it can not allow Jin to participate in the above-said function as he was punished for his visit to the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery during his trip to Pyongyang in May last year and is put under investigation on a charge of violation of the "National Security Law," the statement said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that such behavior of the ministry precisely means denying its existence by itself, the statement expressed disillusion at the attitude of officials of the ministry against national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KCTU can never pardon the ministry for blocking the march for peace and reunification, the statement said, stressing that it would inform all the KCTU members and other people of the above-said fact and wage a struggle to denounce it.

Defence of Global Peace and Security Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- To defend the global peace and security at present is an urgent requirement and task of the times which no one can turn aside from as it is a vital issue related to the destiny of humankind. 
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed article. It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S.-led imperialist forces are becoming evermore undisguised in their moves for aggression and war. This requires all the countries to turn out as one to defend the global peace and security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the U.S.-led imperialists that pose the biggest threat to the global peace and security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the basic requirement for defending the global peace and security to deal a deadlier blow at the staggering U.S. imperialists badly beaten in different parts of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is very important to strengthen the non-aligned movement. The NAM serves as a very effective and strong force in achieving the above-said objective. It is necessary to be vigilant against the imperialist forces' moves to drive a wedge and sow the seeds of dissension among its member countries. It is equally important to give momentum to the trend of the world towards regional cooperation and multi-polarization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is essential to foil the moves of the allies of the U.S. imperialists for aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has emerged a dangerous aggressor force in Asia backed by the U.S. Israel has a scenario to attack the nuclear facilities in Iran. The situation is growing tenser wherever there are forces toeing the U.S. line. It is, therefore, important to pressurize and isolate those forces toeing the U.S. war policy to deter them from running wild, while intensifying the struggle against the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary for each country to build up its own strength to defend the global peace and security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The practical experience gained by the DPRK proves that a country can prevent a war and protect its sovereignty and peace only when it attaches importance to the military affairs and bolster its self-reliant defence capability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year, too, the Korean people will smash the moves of the U.S. imperialists to provoke a new war, defend the peace on the Korean Peninsula and firmly protect the global peace and security, united close with all the anti-imperialist independent forces in the world under the uplifted banner of Songun.

Mass Rallies Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- Mass rallies were held in North Hwanghae and North Hamgyong Provinces to vow to effect a new turn in building a great prosperous powerful nation true to the joint New Year editorial.
 At the rallies reporters and speakers underscored the need to continue to dynamically advance for greater efflorescence of national prosperity along the bright road indicated by the joint New Year editorial in the same spirit as they displayed to make a great leaping forward full of great ambition and confidence last year under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also stressed the need to accelerate the drive to implement the Workers' Party of Korea's policy of effecting a radical innovation in agriculture so as to make an epoch-making advance in solving the food problem and decisively improve the production of consumer goods and, at the same time, lay the firmer foundations for improving the standard of people's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Similar rallies were also held by servicepersons of the Ministry of People's Security and employees of the Ministry of Railways. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Reporters and speakers said at the rallies called for defending as firm as a rock the single-minded unity of the leader, the Party and the people, the security of the Korean-style socialist system and the life and property of the people and well organizing and commanding the railway transport and establishing the strong discipline and order to satisfactorily meet the increasing need for transport.

Korean People's Reverence for Great Leader
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- The people of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea entered the significant New Year with boundless glory and national pride of having the great leader.
 On the morning of the New Year's Day, servicepersons, working people from all walks of life, youth and schoolchildren visited statues of President Kim Il Sung standing on Mansu Hill in Pyongyang and in other parts of the country to offer their New Year's greeting to him and to pledge themselves to build a Juche-oriented great, prosperous and powerful socialist country without fail under the leadership of the great Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They came to have the infinite respect for and trust in him, through life experience, and the firm belief that they would emerge ever-victorious and enjoy boundless happiness under his leadership, in the years when they had performed miraculous wonders upholding the Songun-based politics of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under his Songun-based leadership, the Korean people triumphantly concluded "Arduous March" and the forced march, frustrating the imperialists' moves against the DPRK and are now marching forward to open up a great heyday of Songun Korea full of confidence in victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sovereignty of some countries is mercilessly trampled down by the strong-arm politics and arbitrariness of the imperialists today. This stark reality makes them more clearly realize the correctness of the Songun politics of the Workers' Party of Korea and superiority of the Korean-style socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The progressive people of the world, to say nothing of the Korean people, laud Kim Jong Il, who always leads the Korean revolution along the one road of victory and glory with his Songun politics, as the ever-victorious, iron-willed brilliant commander and the sun of the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people, full of national pride and glory of being led by the great leader, will usher in an all-round efflorescence of national prosperity this year.

Agricultural Working People Vow to Make Epochal Advance
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- The agricultural working people of the DPRK, with high degree of revolutionary enthusiasm and firm resolution, have all responded to the call of the joint New Year editorial for keeping up farming as the great foundation of the country and making an epoch-making advance in solving the food problem for the people.
 Kim Hyok Jin, vice-minister of Agriculture, said in an interview with KCNA that all the ministries, national institutions and people's committees of all levels are giving a priority to providing the agricultural sector with farming materials without condition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He further remarked: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We, in charge of implementing the policy of the Workers' Party of Korea on making a revolution in agriculture, are taking measures to properly distribute crops on the principle of the right crop in the right time and on the right soil and to make a giant stride forward in stockbreeding in close contact with officials of provincial, city and county rural economic sectors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular great efforts are being directed to definitely increasing the organic fertilizer production so as to improve the fertility of soil and positively introducing advanced farming technologies so that the potentials of production foundation may be tapped to the maximum. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tractor accessory factories in Sariwon, Haeju and Jongju are fully supplying various kinds of farm-machine accessory parts to the countryside and solving the raised issues through vigorous mass technical innovation drive. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the farms across the country are striving to wind up the work of repairing, maintaining and securing farm-machine accessories and small farm implements before the farming season. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though there are many difficulties, an epochal advance is certain to be made this year thanks to the Party's policy on making a revolution in agriculture, the scientific accuracy and vitality of which have been proved, and the efforts of the agricultural working people supporting the Songun Korea.
